        <span class="fw-chip" style="background:var(--red-s);color:var(--red)">Bisque ×71</span>
        <span class="fw-chip" style="background:var(--orange-s);color:var(--orange)">Lyonnaise ×65</span>
        <span class="fw-chip" style="background:var(--orange-s);color:var(--orange)">Millefeuille ×58</span>
        <span class="fw-chip" style="background:var(--teal-s);color:var(--teal)">Soffritto ×43</span>
        <span class="fw-chip" style="background:var(--teal-s);color:var(--teal)">Velouté ×39</span>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-top:1rem;font-size:0.76rem;color:var(--text-2);line-height:1.7;background:var(--surface-2);border-radius:var(--r-sm);padding:0.875rem">🎯 <strong style="color:var(--text)">Insight:</strong> Guests who encounter 3+ unfamiliar culinary terms on a single item are <strong style="color:var(--text)">2.4× more likely to order their previous order</strong> rather than explore.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<!-- ══ MAIN COLUMN ══ -->
<div class="col-main mob-active" id="colMain">

